                  <additions>
                     <p>A few lines written in red ink follow the prologue. Below <name
                           type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> has made an attempt
                        to copy these.</p>
                     <p>On the originally blank fol. 1r, a hand from <date notBefore="1500"
                           notAfter="1599">the sixteenth century</date> wrote a love poem in six
                        lines. Due to excising of the leaf, the last part of each line is missing.
                        The poem is published in <bibl>Johnsen &amp; Jón Helgason, <ref
                              type="primary" target="OlHJH">Den store saga om Olav den
                              hellige</ref><biblScope unit="volume">II</biblScope><biblScope
                              unit="page">953</biblScope></bibl> and <bibl>Louis-Jensen, <ref
                              type="primary" target="JonLou1996">Marginalia poetica</ref><biblScope
                                 unit="page">257</biblScope></bibl>. In the latter, an attempt to reconstruct the text has been made.</p> 
                     <p>Further benath a single line reads: <q>Gud v<ex>er</ex>e m<ex>ed</ex> þi<ex>er</ex> baudvar(?)</q></p>
                  </additions>
